para.verbatim: We define three types of bytes: alphabet: english alphabets [a-zA-Z] international: international characters [\x80-\xFF] marker: everything else [^a-zA-Z\x80-\xFF] The input buffer can be thought to contain a series of words delimited by markers. This function works to filter all words that contain at least one international character. All contiguous sequences of markers are replaced by a single space ascii character. This filter applies to all scripts which do not use English characters.

Returns a copy of ``buf`` that retains only the sequences of English alphabet and high byte characters that are not between <> characters. This filter can be applied to all scripts which contain both English characters and extended ASCII characters, but is currently only used by ``Latin1Prober``.
